    <etym xml:lang="ru">Основа čar- (<mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/><w>*k˳el-</w></mentioned>) в
        других иранских языках имеет значение ‘пастись’, ‘пасти скот’, ‘кочевать, пася скот’, вообще
        ‘кочевать’, ‘бродить’: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>čaridan</w><gloss><q>пастись</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><w>čalīdan</w><gloss><q>идти</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>carēdəl</w><gloss><q>пастись</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-balochi"
            ><lang/><w>čarag</w><gloss><q>бродить</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="x-balochi"><w/><gloss><q>пасти скот</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="ku"><lang/><w>čarin</w><gloss><q>пастись</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>vi-čar</w><gloss><q>пребывать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="pal"><w>čaraγ</w><gloss><q>пастбище</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Henning._BBB"/><biblScope>109</biblScope></bibl>), ср. <mentioned
            xml:lang="xcl"><lang/><w>čʼarakʼ</w><gloss><q>пастбище</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
            ><lang/><w>čar-</w><gloss><q>двигаться</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>ходить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>бродить</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>čar-</w><gloss><q>двигаться</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>бродить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>пасти скот</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                ><lang/><w>colo</w><gloss><q>ухаживать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>населять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>жить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                ><w>incola</w><gloss><q>обитатель</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>πέλω</w><gloss><q>двигаться</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>становиться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>быть</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Переход значения ‘пасти
        скот’ → ‘жить’ характеризует скотоводческий народ, каким действительно и были предки осетин.
        Аналогичное семантическое развитие наметилось и в других языках (<mentioned xml:lang="pal"
                ><lang/><w>vi-čār</w><gloss><q>пребывать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>colo</w><gloss><q>жить</q></gloss></mentioned>). Ср. <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_8caryn"/> ‘оживлять’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ænʒaryn"/>
        ‘поджигать’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_card"/> ‘жизнь’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_cærænbon"/> ‘жизнь’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cærdæg"/> ‘проворный’,
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cæræccag"/> ‘долголетний’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_calcæg"/> ‘ремонт’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æʒællag"/>
                ‘бедственный’.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>46,
                78</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>57,
                58</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>23,
                56</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">The stem %ičar%i- (<mentioned xml:lang="ine"
            ><lang/><w>*k˳el-</w></mentioned>) in other Iranian languages has the meaning ‘browse’,
        ‘pasture’, ‘wrangle’; ‘nomadise’, ‘wander’ in general: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>čaridan</w><gloss><q>browse</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><w>čalīdan</w><gloss><q>go</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>carēdəl</w><gloss><q>browse</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-balochi"
            ><lang/><w>čarag</w><gloss><q>wander</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="x-balochi"><w/><gloss><q>pasture</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="ku"><lang/><w>čarin</w><gloss><q>browse</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>vi-čar</w><gloss><q>stay</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="pal"><w>čaraγ</w><gloss><q>pasture-land</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Henning._BBB"/><biblScope>109</biblScope></bibl>), cf. <mentioned
            xml:lang="xcl"><lang/><w>čʼarakʼ</w><gloss><q>pasture-land</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
            ><lang/><w>čar-</w><gloss><q>move</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>walk</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>wander</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>čar-</w><gloss><q>move</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>wander</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>pasture</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                ><lang/><w>colo</w><gloss><q>maintain</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>inhabit</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>live</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                ><w>incola</w><gloss><q>inhabitant</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>πέλω</w><gloss><q>move</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>become</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>be</q></gloss></mentioned>, . The transition of the meaning
        ‘pasture’ → ‘live’ describes cattle-breeding people which the ancestors of the Ossetic
        people really were. A similar semantic development has been outlined in other languages as
        well (<mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>vi-čār</w><gloss><q>stay</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>colo</w><gloss><q>live</q></gloss></mentioned>). Cf.
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_8caryn"/> ‘make alive’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_ænʒaryn"/> ‘put on fire’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_card"/> ‘life’,
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cærænbon"/> ‘life’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cærdæg"
        /> ‘nimble’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cæræccag"/> ‘longliving’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_calcæg"/> ‘reparation’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æʒællag"/>
                ‘disastrous’.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>46,
                78</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>57,
                58</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>23,
                56</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
